A guide to MARDI GRAS in New Orleans:
•this year will be my 10th Mardi Gras… and I can’t wait! As a veteran, here are my tips and tricks 
•There’s a first weekend, called ‘Mardi Gras lite’ that’s just as fun but slightly less crowded - and I’ll be riding that weekend with @kreweoffreret 
•you mostly want to stay uptown, it’s where the locals are and it’s much better. But you won’t see any flashing! That’s just on Bourbon Street
•don’t touch the police horses and don’t get caught peeing in public if you don’t want to end up in jail all weekend
•get yourself downtown on Mardi Gras morning (aka Fat Tuesday); it’s a ton of fun, great costumes, and a party in the streets - you’ll want to end up in the general vicinity of @lafittesblacksmithshopbar 
•there’s not a ton of food available, eat king cake and @raisingcanes 

#mardigras #neworleans #neworleansmardigras #gotothemardigras #mardigrasparade #mardipardi #tulane #uptown #uptownmardigras #krewe #mardigrasoutfit #mardigrasball #mardigrasguide #guidetomardigras #neworleanslife #nola #visitneworleans #visitnola

How to: Mardi Gras like a Local 📿

•most of the best parades are uptown, and they’re not what you pictured. Bourbon St. is for tourists and isn’t what the locals do. 
•the uptown parades are family-friendly… so there’s no flashing (again, that’s downtown on Bourbon)
•there aren’t a lot of bathrooms - but don’t get caught peeing on the street… you’ll get thrown in jail
•don’t sleep on the stuff in between floats! The bands are insanely good 
•there’s not a ton of food options - most places close, so stock up in advance 
•the weather can be 30 or 80… so layer up; and bring comfy shoes because there’s a LOT of walking

Festivities start Feb 10 for what we call “locals weekend”, and then the main event is 6-days long from Thursday Feb 16-Feb 21. Book your tickets now 🛩️

The hit of this year’s Lundi Gras party: caviar topped hash browns. A bunch of friends came over for a day of lawn games, cute puppies running around, lots of @abitabeer , and plenty of good food. In true Mardi Gras style, we had king cakes and @raisingcanes … and everyone was pretty psyched when I surprised them with these bad boys. Super easy to make; I bought frozen hash browns and créme fraîche from @traderjoes and picked up a 5oz container of local caviar from @cajuncaviar (a large jar was more than enough to make about 5 trays of these bites; plenty for about 25 people). 10/10 recommend.

I’m probably at @valsnola at least once a week when I’m home… it’s so laid back, I love the outdoor eating area filled with lush plants, the drinks are strong and the food is good 👍🏼
